SIMPLE: fashion
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fashion
<hw>Fash"ion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>fasoun</ets>, <ets>facioun</ets>, shape, manner, F.
<ets>facon</ets>, orig., a making, fr. L. <ets>factio</ets> a making,
fr. <ets>facere</ets> to make. See <er>Fact</er>, <er>Feat</er>, and cf.
<er>Faction</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The make or form of anything; the style, shape,
appearance, or mode of structure; pattern, model; <as>as, the
<ex>fashion</ex> of the ark, of a coat, of a house, of an altar,
etc.</as>; workmanship; execution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>fashion</qex> of his countenance was altered.</q>
<rj><qau>Luke ix. 29.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I do not like the <qex>fashion</qex> of your garments.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The prevailing mode or style, especially of dress;
custom or conventional usage in respect of dress, behavior, etiquette,
etc.; particularly, the mode or style usual among persons of good
breeding; <as>as, to dress, dance, sing, ride, etc., in the
<ex>fashion</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The innocent diversions in <qex>fashion</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As now existing, <qex>fashion</qex> is a form of social regulation
analogous to constitutional government as a form of political
regulation.</q> <rj><qau>H. Spencer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Polite, fashionable, or genteel life; social
position; good breeding; <as>as, men of <ex>fashion</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Mode of action; method of conduct; manner; custom;
sort; way.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧After his sour <xex>fashion</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>After a fashion</b></col>, <cd>to a certain extent; of a
sort; sort of.</cd> -- <col><b>Fashion piece</b></col>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>one of the timbers which terminate the transom,
and define the shape of the stern.</cd> -- <col><b>Fashion
plate</b></col>, <cd>a pictorial design showing the prevailing style or
a new style of dress.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fashion</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fashion
<hw>Fash"ion</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Fashioned</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Fashioning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>faconner</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To form; to give shape or
figure to; to mold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Here the loud hammer <qex>fashions</qex> female toys.</q>
<rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ingenious art . . . ⟦br⟧
Steps forth to <qex>fashion</qex> and refine the age.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To fit; to adapt; to accommodate; -- with
<xex>to</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Laws ought to be <qex>fashioned</qex> to the manners and
conditions of the people.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To make according to the rule prescribed by
custom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Fashioned</qex> plate sells for more than its weight.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To forge or counterfeit.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fashioning needle</b></col> <fld>(Knitting
Machine)</fld>, <cd>a needle used for widening or narrowing the work and
thus shaping it.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fashionable</ent>⟦br⟧
